**Assessing code changes**

I see that only the TypeScript type has changed and no tests were modified. It might be sufficient for me to run `node --check` for the JavaScript and one-off DB script without conducting a full run. I wonder if I could inspect the summary of the git diff instead of going through the entire list to keep it concise. It's worth running it just to confirm everything is in order!
